==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: spinach beet
<hw>spinach beet</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a beet lacking a
swollen root; it is grown as a vegetable for its edible leaves and
stalks.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> chard, Swiss chard, spinach beet, leaf beet, chard
plant, Beta vulgaris cicla.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><b>2.</b> <def>a plant with long succulent whitish stalks with large
green leaves.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> chard, Swiss chard, spinach beet, leaf
beet.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>spinach blight</ent>⟦br⟧
